_:c5ecdf4f34b5b8df0c0ea175c819d89a a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "\n                        Anders Svensson, born in Nävlinge socken in 1849, was ordained a \n                        priest in Lund in 1874, and became a missionary for\n                        Swedish Evangelical Mission in Eritrea in 1877. He was a teacher at the school outside\n                        Imkullo. From 1885 to 1897, he was the head of the school, \n                        which from 1890 was located in Zazega. \n                        As the chairman of the missionary conference (missionskonferens)\n                        from 1886 to 1913, he travelled through the entire area where the SEM was active, ordaining priests and\n                        consecrating churches and graveyards.\n                        He is buried in Zazega. According to ,\n                        he was locally known as ቀሺ ሜንሶን\n                        (Qašši Menson),\n                        which is the name attested in Uppsala, Uppsala University Library, Q 15:24 o.\n                    " .
<https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14576AndersSvensson> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P4_has_time_span> _:c5ecdf4f34b5b8df0c0ea175c819d89a ;
